---
title: Middle Eastern Ground Beef
category: 
---

## Ingredients

- 2 lbs. ground beef
- 1 large onion, chopped
- 4 garlic cloves
- 1.5 tsp salt
- 1/2 tsp coarse ground black pepper

- 1/4 C water
- 2 Tbsp ground corriander
- 2 tsp. ground cumin
- 1 1/2 tsp. ground cinnamon
- 1 tsp. allspice
- 1/2 tsp. cayene pepper
- 1/2 tsp. dried mint leaves (optional)
- 1/4 tsp. ground ginger

## Method

1. Ground beef, onion, garlic, salt, peper in pan on medium high. 8-10 min, breaking apart, until browned.
2. In small cup: water, coriander, cumin, cinnamon, allspice, cayenne, mint, ginger. Mix well.
3. Mix into beef. Serve over rice, with hummus and tomatoes on the side. 
